<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-357-410  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 357 410.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Engineering Times  May 26 1989 n540 p80(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>EE jobs are far and few between: industrial automation.andO;(electronics engineers)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Rostky, George.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The employment opportunities for electronics engineers (EEs) inindustrial automation companies are limited for several reasons,including the small size of the typical firm, smaller salariesthan in other markets for EEs, and selection of other firms toprovide EE services.andP;  Salaries generally range in the $20,000 to$50,000 area.andP;  The current EE hiring policies of several firms arebriefly described, including Brain Power Inc, Rhino Robots,Klinger Scientific Co, Industrial Engineering and Equipment Co'sSolitech division, Motion Science Inc, Affiliated ManufacturersInc, and International Robomotion Intelligence.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Employment OpportunityElectrical EngineeringTrendsIndustrial Engineering.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>